Basic Education PS Julius Jwan interacts with KCPE candidate at Sun and Shield School in Rongai, Nakuru County on March 9, 2022. [Harun Wathari, Standard]  Education Cabinet Secretary George Magoha is expected to release the 2021 KCPE results today (Monday, March 28).  Some 1,225,507 candidates enrolled for the exam, which was written between March 7 and March 9.  Parents or guardians can check their children’s KCPE results by sending the candidate’s index number, followed by the initials KCPE to the SMS code 20076.  The service, which is available on all mobile networks, charges Sh25 per request. Due to high demand, there could be a delay in returning result slip via SMS.  If you know any KCPE candidate who has scored at least 400 marks in the 2021 exam, we’d like to feature him or her in The Standard newspaper and The Standard website.   Send us his or her name, picture, index number, marks scored, name of school and the county he or she is from. You can send the details through the phone number 0740 881 250.  By Standard Reporter | 3 hours ago By Augustine Oduor | 14 hours ago By Augustine Oduor | 14 hours ago By Lillian Chepkoech | 14 hours ago